50|$|With {{increased}} {{concerns about}} nuclear waste, breeding <b>fuel</b> <b>cycles</b> became interesting again {{because they can}} reduce actinide wastes, particularly plutonium and minor actinides. Breeder reactors are designed to fission the actinide wastes as fuel, and thus convert them to more fission products.|$|R
